John Gerin performed an autopsy on this man, whose body was dissolved with sulfuric
acid after authorities decided that quicklime wouldn’t work fast enough. This man used the
alias “Fred (+) Nieman” during a meeting in the house of the editor of the Free Society,
Abraham Isaak; at that meeting, this man sought to meet with Emma (*) Goldman. Gaetano
Bresci inspired this man, who concealed an Iver Johnson revolver at the Temple of Music during the
Pan-American Exposition in Buffalo. For the points, name this anarchist who, in 1901, assassinated
William McKinley.=====
Leon Frank Czolgosz =====